com.i2group.apollo.searchservice.transport

Class SearchSummary

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.searchservice.transport.SearchSummary

  • public final class SearchSummary
extends Object
    A summary of the results of a search or dumbbell search operation. Clients must retrieve a SearchSummary before retrieving the SearchResults themselves.
    Since:
    1.0

      • getResultCount

        public Integer getResultCount()
        Gets a count of the results referenced by this SearchSummary.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if:
        • The number of results exceeds the maximum configured, or
        • The search is unbounded, or
        • The user has insufficient permissions.
        Since:
        3.0

      • getItemTypeCounts

        public Collection<ItemTypeCount> getItemTypeCounts()
        Gets the ItemTypeCounts for this SearchSummary.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if the user has insufficient permissions.

      • getSetIdentifier

        public ItemIdentifierAndVersion getSetIdentifier()
        Gets the ItemIdentifierAndVersion of the owner of the set that all the Items in the SearchResults are a member of. (The set owner itself appears in the getItems() return value.)
        Returns:
        See above, or null if:
        • The Items in the SearchResults are not constrained by a set.
        • This SearchSummary is being returned as the result of a dumbbell search.

      • getItems

        public Items getItems()
        Gets Items including the Item referenced by getSetIdentifier() and any other Items related to it.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if the Items in the SearchResults are not constrained by a set.
